results.name: Let p be a prime that has a primitive root between 0 and p that is not also a primitive root of p^2 (A060503); sequence gives smallest such primitive root.
example: 14 is a primitive root of 29 but not of 29^2.
results.author: _Jud McCranie_, Mar 22 2001
